719430f-a.title: Manhattan: East Broadway - Canal Street
719430f-a.text:
At the intersection of East Broadway (left) and Canal Street (right),
showing a view westward from Rutgers Street. On the extreme right, appears
a portion of Seward Park. In the background on Canal Street, is seen the
Canal Street station of the Second Ave. Elevated Line, and on East Broadway, a
portion of the Manhattan Bridge.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
